This is a collection of sound files and associated software, collected
by Bill Schottstaedt (with much help from Peter Kabal) from various
public sources.  The files included are:

32bit.sf            IRCAM le float
8svx-8.snd          8SVX 8-bit
Fnonull.aif	    9 samples, AIFF-C file with COMM chunk declaring 92 bytes 
                       (1 byte longer than actual file length), SSND with 9 bytes, 
                       missing trailing fill byte. -- an invalid AIFF file.
Pmiscck.aif	    9 samples, AIFF-C file with an odd length intermediate chunk (type XxXx)
Pmiscck.wav	    9 samples, WAVE file with an odd length intermediate chunk (type XxXx)
Pnossnd.aif	    0 samples, AIFF-C file with 0 samples (no SSND chunk)
Poffset.aif	    9 samples, AIFF-C file, SSND chunk has a 5 byte offset to the data and trailing junk in the SSND chunk
Porder.aif	    9 samples, AIFF-C file with SSND chunk ahead of the COMM chunk
Ptjunk.aif	    9 samples, AIFF-C file with trailing junk after the FORM chunk
Ptjunk.wav	    9 samples, WAVE file with trailing junk after the RIFF chunk
a16.pvf             PVF ascii (16-bit)
addf8.afsp          NeXT/Sun 16-bit linear with AFsp header extension
addf8.d             SPPACK
addf8.dwd           DiamondWare
addf8.nh            raw (no header)
addf8.nsp	    CSL 8kHz 16-bit
addf8.sd            ESPS 16-bit
addf8.sf_mipseb     IRCAM 16-bit
addf8.sf_sun        IRCAM 16-bit
addf8.sf_vax_b      IRCAM 16-bit
addf8.wav           RIFF 16-bit
aebass.krz	    Kurzweil
aifc-float.snd      AIFC float
aiff-16.snd         AIFF 16-bit
aiff-8.snd          AIFF 8-bit (signed)
alaw.aifc           AIFC alaw
alaw.wav	    RIFF alaw
anno.aif            AIFF with ANNO chunk
bad_srate.snd       these are various messed-up headers (for error testing)
bad_srate.riff
bad_srate.nist
bad_srate.aifc
bad_length.nist
bad_length.aifc
badform.aiff
bad_chans.snd
bad_chans.riff
bad_chans.nist
bad_chans.aifc
b.sd                ESPS little endian unknown format
b16.pvf             PVF 16-bit binary
b32.pvf             PVF 32-bit binary (all these from the pvf conversion utilities)
b8.pvf              PVF 8-bit binary
canyon.sd           ESPS 16KHz
caruso.asc          Octave/WaveLab ASCII file.
ce-c3.w02           Yamaha TX-16
clbonef.wav         RIFF 32-bit float
crash.au            Next/Sun mulaw
daj.sam		    Sambox 
d40130.aif          AIFF version
d40130.dsf          Delusion Digital Sound File
d40130.fsm          Farandole Composer WaveSample
d40130.iff          SVX8 version
d40130.pat          Gravis patch (signed 16-bit)
d40130.sds          MIDI sample dump
d40130.sdx          Sample dump exchange (little endian data -- wood.sdx=big endian)
d40130.sf           IRCAM (VAX id, little endian header, big endian data -- is this correct?)
d40130.smp          SMP le short
d40130.sou          SB Studio II
d40130.stm          "STM" output from SFconvert 1.6 (is this the Amiga stm format?)
d40130.st3          Digiplayer ST3
d40130.uwf          Ultratracker wavesample
d40130.voc          VOC version
d40130.w00          Yamaha TX-16
d40130.wav          Wave (RIFF) original (Convert 1.4 used to create all the rest of this name)
