If anyone has examples (preferably short) of other header/data formats,
please send me a copy.  Thanks to Peter Kabal for providing a number
of these examples.

See sndlib.tar.gz for code to read most of these file types.

The documentation included:

aiff and aifc       AIFF specs
riff                RIFF (wav) specs
nist                NIST specs
AudioFormats.*      audio formats FAQ
forms.txt           More documentation from http://www.wotsit.demon.co.uk/music.htm
wavecomp.htm        RIFF stuff in HTML format
asf.txt             ASF junk
avi.html            AVI doc
sf2.txt             SoundFont 2 doc
rf64.pdf	    EBU RF64 spec
bwf.pdf             EBU BWF spec

bil@ccrma.stanford.edu

